WEBVTT

00:00.578 --> 00:02.394
<i>Previously on
"Legends of Tomorrow"...</i>

00:02.573 --> 00:03.895
Is this your new girlfriend?

00:03.896 --> 00:05.180
- Um, yeah.
- Mm-hmm.

00:05.192 --> 00:06.793
You and I dating would
be totally weird.

00:06.794 --> 00:07.500
Totally weird.

00:07.920 --> 00:09.558
Wow, that's beautiful.

00:11.090 --> 00:13.080
Step away from the creature,
miss.

00:13.090 --> 00:16.090
You murdered him!

00:19.250 --> 00:21.420
Hank is running
some secret project.

00:21.440 --> 00:23.260
He's not just taking
the fugitives.

00:23.270 --> 00:24.510
He's testing on them.

00:24.590 --> 00:25.930
I don't need you anymore.

00:25.940 --> 00:27.850
I don't need you anymore,
either.

00:30.890 --> 00:31.820
What did you do?

00:31.900 --> 00:32.850
I'm sorry.

00:34.000 --> 00:40.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:44.490 --> 00:46.410
Maybe I shouldn't intrude.

00:46.480 --> 00:48.790
Nate needs all of our
support right now.

00:48.870 --> 00:50.540
Well, what am I supposed
to say to him?

00:50.610 --> 00:52.460
"Sorry the woman I've been
exchanging love letters with

00:52.540 --> 00:54.210
in prison killed your dad"?

00:54.280 --> 00:56.130
They ought to put that
on a condolence card.

00:56.210 --> 00:59.710
Look, we are going inside
and we are going to strive

00:59.790 --> 01:03.010
with grace to help our friend
cope with his loss.

01:03.080 --> 01:04.720
<i>Damn it.</i>

01:04.790 --> 01:06.520
Here, let me help.

01:09.130 --> 01:13.140
Hey, uh, thanks for
sticking around this past week.

01:13.150 --> 01:15.440
What are pretend
girlfriends for?

01:15.510 --> 01:19.070
My mom's gonna be so crushed
when I tell her we broke up.

01:19.140 --> 01:22.490
Then don't.

01:22.500 --> 01:24.280
I... I mean,
she's going through a lot.

01:24.360 --> 01:26.780
We can pretend break up
any time we want.

01:32.840 --> 01:37.330
We should, um... we should
probably get out there.

01:37.340 --> 01:39.180
You ready for this?

01:43.710 --> 01:45.020
Oh, Nathaniel.

01:45.090 --> 01:46.760
I need you to make
a toast later.

01:46.840 --> 01:51.180
Tell everyone what
an amazing man your father was.

01:51.190 --> 01:53.180
Yeah, Mom, I don't think
that's a great idea.

01:53.190 --> 01:55.060
What?
Of course it is.

01:55.140 --> 01:57.150
And Zari, I am so glad
that you're here

01:57.220 --> 01:59.570
for Nathaniel
to lean on right now.

01:59.650 --> 02:01.440
Yeah, um, you know me.

02:01.520 --> 02:04.530
I'm... I'm his rock.

02:04.600 --> 02:07.030
I can't.
I... I can't face him.

02:07.040 --> 02:08.910
Wait... wait.

02:17.460 --> 02:19.630
I hope you're not
stress-eating, squire.

02:21.090 --> 02:22.420
I don't know what else to do.

02:22.500 --> 02:23.800
I can't believe this
is happening.

02:25.890 --> 02:28.090
You feel the energy
in this room?

02:28.170 --> 02:30.730
It's like sitting on
a keg of dynamite.

02:30.810 --> 02:32.390
You see, wakes are
notorious soft spots

02:32.400 --> 02:34.310
where the supernatural
meets the living world.

02:34.380 --> 02:36.020
See Nate's aunt?

02:36.090 --> 02:38.560
That particular prayer
is to ward off evil spirits

02:38.570 --> 02:43.980
and they've covered the mirrors,
so the bad lads can't get in.

02:44.060 --> 02:45.400
Well, that's creepy.

02:45.410 --> 02:47.820
Yeah, well,
creepy is my business.

02:51.440 --> 02:53.420
And it looks like
business is good.

03:01.950 --> 03:03.590
Oh!

03:03.600 --> 03:06.550
Nate, Nate, I'm... I'm sorry.
I'm... I'm so sorry.

03:06.620 --> 03:08.010
No, it's... it's okay, Ray.

03:08.080 --> 03:10.010
No, no, no, it's not.

03:10.090 --> 03:11.940
I keep giving Nora
second chances and

03:12.010 --> 03:14.310
she goes and does this.

03:14.380 --> 03:16.680
Look, you thought
Nora could change

03:16.760 --> 03:20.900
and I never thought my dad would
be torturing magical creatures,

03:20.970 --> 03:24.120
so I guess... I guess
we're both wrong.

03:25.690 --> 03:27.690
Can't believe you're
the one comforting me.

03:27.770 --> 03:29.900
Oh, come on.
I love you, bro.

03:29.980 --> 03:31.280
That's never gonna change.

03:33.610 --> 03:34.790
Love you, too.

03:45.620 --> 03:47.920
Oh, no.
Don't, no-no-no, don't.

03:48.000 --> 03:49.470
Don't, don't, don't do it, Ray.

03:49.480 --> 03:51.590
Don't... you're gonna do it.

03:51.670 --> 03:53.310
You're gonna do it.

03:57.110 --> 03:58.100
Nora?

03:58.841 --> 04:03.680
